<font color="Navy" size="+1">PURPOSE</font><br>
<p><li>To inform the members and the public about the life, faith and work of the Diocese of Chicago, its congregations, agencies and organizations.
<li>To equip the clergy and lay members of the diocese for mission and ministry.
<li>To promote the mission of the diocese, the Episcopal Church, and the Anglican Communion.</p>

<font color="Navy" size="+1">MANAGEMENT</font><br>
<p>The operation of the diocesan web site is the responsibility of the Office of Communications under the direct supervision of the director of communications.</p>

<font color="Navy" size="+1">OWNERSHIP</font><br>
<p>All content on the site is the property of the Diocese of Chicago, unless otherwise copyrighted. Any reproduction, publication, distribution or transmission of this content is prohibited without the written permission of the Diocese of Chicago.</p>

<font color="Navy" size="+1">CONTENT</font><br>
<p>Material submitted for publication will be subject to the standards and schedule of the Office of Communications. The Office of Communications reserves the right to edit material according to style, space and format requirements. </p>

<font color="Navy" size="+1">DISCLAIMER</font><br>
<p>Acceptance of material does not constitute a promise of publication.  The Office of Communications does not warrant the accuracy of information submitted for publication. Publication of information does not constitute an official endorsement by the Diocese of Chicago.</p>

<font color="Navy" size="+1">PRIVACY</font><br>
<p>The Diocese of Chicago will not release personal information, including email addresses, home addresses and phone numbers, to third parties unless authorized by the owner. As a matter of policy, the Diocese of Chicago does not publish home addresses or the names of minors appearing in photographs on the site. Contact information, unless specified otherwise, will be assumed as intended and authorized for publication.</p>

<p><i>(adopted by the Communications Commission of the Diocese of Chicago April 24, 2001)</i></p>

